{"questionId":"11123","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Polymers have a wide variety of uses but their disposal can be problematic.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">The infrared (IR) spectrum of polyethene is given.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img style=\"margin-right:auto;margin-left:auto;display:block;\" src=\"__IMG__/74b6f4a77f9449d6eff104c99f31730500c3bb1f.png\" width=\"657\" height=\"520\"></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Suggest how the IR spectrum of polychloroethene would differ, using section 26 of the data booklet.</span></span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">«strong additional» absorption at 600–800 «cm<sup>–1</sup>»&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>","meta":{"questionId":"11123","referenceCode":"19M.3.sl.TZ2.5b","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"The infrared (IR) spectrum of polyethene is given. Suggest how the IR spectrum of polychloroethene would differ, using section 26 of the data booklet.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 11: Measurement and data processing","11.3 Spectroscopic identification of organic compounds","Core","Topic 11: Measurement and data processing"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}